  "text": "In general, the experimental procedure consisted of two stages: firstly S. terebinthifolius fruits were dried, and secondly morphological and physicochemical parameters were characterized, and volatile compounds were extracted from the dried product. The drying of S. terebinthifolius fruits was carried out in a pilot thin-layer dryer (tray dryer), described by Silva et al. [CITATION_1] . The dryer receives atmospheric air from a fan, and air flow is adjusted by a manual valve. The air heating system consists of four electrical resistors connected to a temperature control system. A fixed bed thickness of 1 cm was used in the experiments. Relative humidity (RH) was measured continuously throughout the experiments using a thermohygrometer (Ummi5). In each drying assay, drying kinetics and rate (see (3)) were analyzed.",
